HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta samu karin mutane 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar yawan mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS da kashi 14 cikin ɗari.
Ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne ke fama da wannan cuta a ƙasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na shekara ta 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane kusan 40,000.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka na kamuwa da cutar ta hanyar jima'i ne, kuma hakan ya nuna cewa yanayin da ake ciki yanzu ya canja.
A wasu wurare a ƙasar Sin, cutar HIV tana yaduwa da sauri ta wajen ƙarin jini.
Amma, wannan hanyar ce ta kawo ƙarshen kamuwa da cutar HIV, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na ƙasar Sin a wani taro da aka yi a lardin Yunnan.
A kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin yana ƙaruwa da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An haramta luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma har yanzu ana nuna wa LGBTI nuna wariya.
Bincike ya nuna cewa domin ɗabi'ar da kasar take bi, kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna aure.
A yawancin lokuta, rashin kāriya da ake yi wa waɗannan maza da mata da ke da jima'i da juna ne ke sa mutane kamuwa da cututtuka.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar kanjamau ga kowa a kasar a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
